                            <comment id="14649567" author="stefank" created="Thu, 15 Feb 2024 00:42:06 -0800"  >Fix Request&lt;br/&gt;
This is a small, trivial fix that only removes a noise log line. Without this fix our UL log files can become massive, if the user runs with -Xlog:monitordeflation=debug.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The log line used to warn about an unexpected state of object monitors, but with recent rewrites to the monitor deflation code, this state is not uncommon anymore (by design), so it is better to not log messages about it.</comment>
